&gt; failure... I should melt you to scrap right now for your insolent 
&gt; behaviour, but I have a better idea.&quot; a small smile catches the 
&gt; edges of Hydras&#39; mouth.
&gt; 
&gt; &quot;Maxima dear, begin work on the Blackstrom clone.&quot; Hydras says with 
&gt; a short glance back at the female predacon. &quot;Implant a virus into 
&gt; the clone to lay dormant until they try to reformat the Blackstorm 
&gt; clone and return her to Nightlight.&quot;
&gt; 
&gt; The Predacon commander turns back to the newly returned 
&gt; Wolfenstein. &quot;Ah yes, now for your part. It is your job to escort 
&gt; the clone on a recon mission which vectors nearest to the Maximal 
&gt; base. I&#39;m sure their sensors will pick you up. It will be your job 
&gt; to make sure the clone gets into their hands safely, and I don&#39;t 
&gt; mean just hand it to them. Make it real, trick them.&quot;
&gt; 
&gt; &quot;Oh, and one more thing.&quot; Hydras&#39;s hand slides into his arm and a 
&gt; spiked semi-sphere forms around his hand - Hydras Fusion Cannon - 
&gt; and points it at the new but old Predacon. (The cannon does not 
&gt; always fire at full strength, just in case you&#39;re wondering if 
&gt; hydras is willing to level his base to get back at wolfy =p)
&gt; 
&gt; &quot;Perceptor,&quot; He tosses a small explosive device to the other 
&gt; bot, &quot;Insert this at the back of Wolfenstein&#39;s neck.&quot; He turns to 
&gt; Wolfy, &quot;If you disobey, you will never disobey again.&quot;
&gt; 
&gt; Perceptor moves towards Wolfenstein following Hydras commands.
